      "writtenOn": "2026-05-26T01:11:28Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "yeah, you said in the original commit message that these are for the SONiC project, but I was asking about the networking use case for tunnels that behave this way.\n\nOne could view your requirements as a new tunnel type, or you could model then as properties (uni-directionality and promiscuity) of the current types. I want to understand why the networking use case requires them so we can best determine the fit. For example, perhaps there is a use case for uni-directionality and promiscuity on their own and we wouldn\u0027t want to introduce new type for that too.",
      "parentUuid": "184d2cf2_81d15ee3",
      "revId": "8e394e0e53798b495330630d0ede3ec3c49c5b8c",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
